race.comment: Very even but perhaps the one with least convictions is I LOVERAIN (4). Hit the line hard fresh over 1200m to place and looks well placed this class. Will give a start but wind up late and if there is any rain it will only enhance his chances. PULAMBI (10) has been given a let-up since racing over further last couple. This is easier and does have a good record back at home. Should also be winding up late. REFRESHING (7) is another with better form than it looks. Comes back a notch and will be in this for a long way. HOT OFF (6) was safely held at Halidon latest but ran very well in town the start prior. This more suitable and will take catching off the inside gate.
